title: US man purchases $395,000 cliffside home despite erosion warnings

description: The South African band Kiffness created a parody song called "Eating the Cats" that mocks former US President Donald Trump's false claim about immigrants eating pets in Springfield, Ohio. The video has gone viral and features edited audio of Trump with auto-tuned animal sounds. Proceeds from streaming will benefit the Clark County SPCA.
title: Trump's 'they're eating the cats' has now turned into a viral song, watch

description: NASA astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore shared their relief after the Boeing Starliner spacecraft safely landed in New Mexico. During a live press conference from the ISS, they discussed their extended mission, lessons learned, and upcoming handover to Expedition 72 astronauts Nick and Alex. The astronauts are scheduled to return to Earth aboard a SpaceX Crew Dragon in February.
title: 'Lessons learned': Stranded astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore on Boeing's return to earth

description: India and Pakistan will meet in their last league match of the Asian Champions Trophy in Moqi, China. Both teams are unbeaten; India have won all four matches while Pakistan have two wins and two draws. Both the teams have already secured a place in the semifinals, with three other teams competing for the remaining two spots.
title: Ind vs Pak: Why is India hot favourite for the ACT hockey match
SC to study if rules can be set for swift probe into plaints about missing girls

description: Former CSK batter Subramaniam Badrinath recounted a rare instance of MS Dhoni losing his temper during an IPL match against RCB. CSK, chasing a modest target of 110 odd runs, unexpectedly lost the game. Dhoni showed visible frustration in the dressing room post-match, which was unusual for the typically composed captain.
title: 'Kicked bottle...': Ex-CSK batter reveals rare moment of Dhoni losing cool

description: Mohammad Sufiyan from Telangana returned home after being tricked by a fraudulent agent into joining a private Russian army to fight in Ukraine. Along with three others from Karnataka, he endured severe conditions and constant fear. Their families sought help from the Indian government, leading to their rescue.
title: 'Made to work for 15 hours a day, were fired at if we slacked off'

description: Gautam Gambhir, the new head coach of India's cricket team, prepares for a home Test series against Bangladesh with his coaching staff. Key focuses include player readiness after a long break, pace bowler rotation, and crucial selection decisions in batting and wicketkeeping positions. This series is vital for World Test Championship qualification.
title: Closed-door camp before first Test vs Bangladesh

description: Agra's historical monuments, including the Taj Mahal, have been significantly damaged by continuous rain over 48 hours. The Archaeological Survey of India is investigating water seepage from the main dome and flooding in nearby gardens. Additional historical sites such as Agra Fort and Fatehpur Sikri have also sustained minor damage from the heavy rainfall.
title: After incessant rain, water leaking from Taj dome, garden flooded; ASI on alert
Hindu side's plea for repairs in Gyanvapi basement nixed
7-time winner Indore put in 'Golden Club', barred from clean city ranking

description: In Yadgir district of Karnataka, fifty Dalit families are reportedly enduring a social boycott after a minor girl's parents filed sexual assault charges against an upper caste man. Following the man's arrest, village leaders imposed the boycott. Authorities are currently mediating to resolve the issue and prevent further ostracism.
title: 50 Dalit families boycotted for Pocso case on upper caste man
You not only won medals but changed mahaul too, PM Modi tells Paralympians

description: Donald Trump has promised mass deportations from Springfield, Ohio, if re-elected, alleging without evidence that Haitian migrants are consuming pets. Local officials and experts dispute these claims and highlight the migrants' positive impact. Governor Mike DeWine announced a $2.5 million initiative to improve healthcare services strained by the migrant population.
title: Trump vows 'large deportations' in US amid false claims of Haitians eating pets

description: Former Pakistan captain Moin Khan has called on Indian cricket legends to persuade the BCCI to separate sports from politics, emphasizing that fans would benefit from cricket matches between India and Pakistan. He has voiced concerns about India's reluctance to travel to Pakistan for the ICC Champions Trophy in 2025.
title: 'If India do not come, then Pakistan should...': Ex-captain's strong warning
After Shimla, Mandi erupts with demand to raze mosque
Thrashed for 'molesting' kid on train, rail staffer dies
Fake cop gets woman lawyer to strip, part with Rs 50,000
3 more fugitives held for Mhow rape, assault on Armymen
50 Dalit families boycotted for Pocso case on upper caste man
‘Caged parrot’ rap haunts CBI after 11 years

description: Liam Livingstone's 87 off 47 balls led England to a three-wicket victory over Australia at Sophia Gardens, tying the T20 series at 1-1. Jacob Bethell's crucial contribution of 44 runs helped stabilize the innings after early setbacks. The decisive final match is scheduled for Sunday in Manchester.
title: 2nd T20I: Livingstone leads England to thrilling victory over Australia

description: The Department of Telecommunications has mandated that at least 50% local content is required for 36 identified telecom products in public procurement. This measure aims to promote domestic manufacturing and applies to central government entities and projects funded by the Universal Service Obligation Fund. Stakeholders are invited to submit comments on the draft notification within 15 days.
title: Telecom department comes with new 'Make in India' rules for these 36 products

description: EU antitrust regulators are considering hefty fines for Google's anti-competitive practices in its adtech business. A breakup order is not currently planned but remains a future possibility if issues persist. The decision may be announced in the coming months, following Margrethe Vestager's departure from office in November.
title: How European Union may have 'bad' but not 'dangerous' news for Google

description: Arvind Kejriwal's release from jail after receiving bail from the Supreme Court in the excise policy case is set to strengthen AAP ahead of elections and revive governance in Delhi. Despite restrictions on his movements, Kejriwal will oversee crucial policy decisions and ensure that administrative work continues smoothly.
title: Delhi gets its CM back: How Kejriwal's return will impact Haryana polls
